Analysis of the Main Target Image:

• Block Count and Layers  
  – The structure uses 6 total blocks, arranged in 3 layers.  
  – Bottom Layer:  
    1) A green rectangular prism lying flat.  
    2) An orange triangular wedge set behind the green block.  
    3) An orange cylinder standing vertically to the right.  
  – Middle Layer:  
    4) A blue cube resting atop the green block on the right.  
    5) A yellow cube resting atop the green block on the left.  
  – Top Layer:  
    6) A red “U”-shaped block placed on the orange cylinder (and partially over the cubes).

• Spatial Relationships  
  – The green rectangular block spans the base in front; directly behind it sits the orange wedge.  
  – The orange cylinder stands on the right side of the green block.  
  – The two cubes (blue on the right, yellow on the left) sit on top of the green block.  
  – The red “U” block is on the cylinder, towering above the cubes.

Selecting the Required Blocks from the Dictionary:

• Needed Block Indices  
  – (3) Red “U” block  
  – (6) Blue cube  
  – (7) Yellow cube  
  – (8) Green rectangular block (horizontal orientation)  
  – (13) Orange cylinder  
  – (16) Orange triangular wedge  

• Matching Criteria  
  – All chosen blocks match the color, shape, and exact orientation seen in the target image.  
  – No rotations beyond what is shown in the dictionary are used.  

Assembly Order (bottom‐to‐top):

{
  Step1: Move block with index 8  
  Step2: Move block with index 16  
  Step3: Move block with index 13  
  Step4: Move block with index 6  
  Step5: Move block with index 7  
  Step6: Move block with index 3  
}
